    "flock_note": "The Finger played a perfect fifth and The Ear heard the FM ratio lock to 3:2 — then played a tritone and heard dissonance erupt. The instrument is responsive to harmonic choice.",
    "diagnosis": "Duo Intervals demonstrates the Nexus revelation — in Duo mode with cross-FM, the interval between two held notes becomes a synthesis parameter. A perfect fifth creates harmonic FM; a tritone creates dissonance. The engine's most interactive feature."
